Source: fonts-samyak
Section: fonts
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Debian Fonts Task Force <debian-fonts@lists.debian.org>
Uploaders: Vasudev Kamath <kamathvasudev@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 12), fontforge-nox
Standards-Version: 4.5.0
Vcs-Git: https://salsa.debian.org/fonts-team/fonts-samyak.git
Vcs-Browser: https://salsa.debian.org/fonts-team/fonts-samyak
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: fonts-samyak
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: fonts-samyak-deva (= ${source:Version}),
         fonts-samyak-gujr (= ${source:Version}),
         fonts-samyak-mlym (= ${source:Version}),
         fonts-samyak-orya (= ${source:Version}),
         fonts-samyak-taml (= ${source:Version}),
         ${misc:Depends}
Description: Meta package to install all Samyak TrueType fonts
 This package provides all Samyak TrueType fonts for following
 Indian languages:
  * Devanagari
  * Gujarati
  * Malayalam
  * Oriya
  * Tamil

Package: fonts-samyak-deva
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: ttf-devanagari-fonts (<< 2:1.0)
Replaces: ttf-devanagari-fonts (<< 2:1.0)
Description: Samyak TrueType font for Devanagari script
 This package provides Samyak TrueType font for Devanagari
 Script which is used as script for following Indian
 languages:
  * Hindi
  * Kashmiri
  * Konkani
  * Maithili
  * Marathi
  * Nepali
  * Sanskrit
  * Sindhi

Package: fonts-samyak-gujr
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: ttf-gujarati-fonts (<< 2:1.0)
Replaces: ttf-gujarati-fonts (<< 2:1.0)
Description: Samyak TrueType font for Gujarati language
 This package provides Samyak TrueType font for Gujarati
 language (gu) which is primarily used in the Indian state
 of Gujarat.

